  "prompt_text": "Write a function to serialize and deserialize a binary tree. Explain your encoding scheme.",
  "response_text": "To serialize and deserialize a binary tree, we can use a pre-order traversal approach. In pre-order traversal, we visit the root node first, then recursively traverse the left subtree, and finally the right subtree. This method ensures that each node is visited exactly once, and the structure of the tree can be reconstructed from the serialized string.\n\n### Serialization Function\n\nThe serialization function will convert the binary tree into a string representation using pre-order traversal. Each node's value will be separated by commas, and null nodes will be represented by \"null\".\n\n```python\nclass TreeNode:\n    def __init__(self, x):\n        self.val = x\n        self.left = None\n        self.right = None\n\ndef serialize(root):\n    if not root:\n        return \"null,\"\n    \n    return f\"{root.val},{serialize(root.left)}{serialize(root.right)}\"\n```\n\n### Deserialization Function\n\nThe deserialization function will reconstruct the binary tree from the serialized string. We split the string by commas and recursively build the tree based on the values.\n\n```python\ndef deserialize(data):\n    def helper(nodes):\n        val = next(nodes)\n        if val == \"null\":\n            return None\n        node = TreeNode(int(val))\n        node.left = helper(nodes)\n        node.right = helper(nodes)\n        return node\n    \n    nodes = iter(data.split(\",\"))\n    return helper(nodes)\n```\n\n### Explanation of Encoding Scheme\n\n- **Pre-order Traversal**: The tree is traversed in a way that the root is processed before its children. This ensures that the structure of the tree is preserved in the serialized string.\n- **Null Nodes**: Null nodes are represented as \"null\" to distinguish them from actual node values.\n- **Comma Separation**: Each node's value and null markers are separated by commas to facilitate easy parsing during deserialization.\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```python\n# Example Tree\n#     1\n#    / \\\n#   2   3\n#      / \\\n#     4   5\n\nroot = TreeNode(1)\nroot.left = TreeNode(2)\nroot.right = TreeNode(3)\nroot.right.left = TreeNode(4)\nroot.right.right = TreeNode(5)\n\n# Serialize\nserialized = serialize(root)\nprint(serialized)  # Output: \"1,2,null,null,3,4,null,null,5,null,null,\"\n\n# Deserialize\ndeserialized_root = deserialize(serialized)\n```\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 7\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 7\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
